<TITLE> BSF kidnaps BDR man </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sylhet, Feb 04 (bdnews24.com)  Indian border guards kidnapped a member of Bangladesh Rifles (BDR) from Jaintapur in Sylhet district on Thursday morning. Lt Col. Khandker Zahirul Alam, Commanding officer of 21 Rifles Battalion, told bdnews24.com that a 15-20-member group of Indian Border Security Force (BSF) entered about 50-metre inside the Bangladesh territory near the border at Jaintapur at around 10 am. They fired two shots injuring BDR nayek Mujibur Rahman, he said, adding: "The BSF members kidnapped him when BDR men tried to resist them." Zahirul said he had information that Mujibur was being tortured and he didn't hear back from his BSF counterpart for a flag meeting until hursday afternoon. bd
